<span class=title> Epics;  Who, what, where?</span><hr size=1> After reading GreyD's post.  (Thank you sir, may I have another!)  I started looking.  I saw Kalamr's post about Chardok and I was wondering who else is needing help with epics, or other quests.<br>
<br>
Please post here, or start another thread )if you wish) with the work you need to finish your epic.  I know that there are many encounters that can be done with two people, and I am willing to help anyone get closer to their epic.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for Me:<br>
<br>
I've done all the foraging/easy stuff with my epic, and got the Jade Reaver in my first CoM raid. I need four more fights to complete:<br>
<br>
1.  Dark Elves in East Karana.  Easy fight, one group of 50+ should do it.  I spawn the Mobs, so it can be done any time.  I'm going to be posting a request for help on a specific night in the Raid section as soon as I can figure out when I can do this.  I bet I could even do this with three people if I had an Enchanter and a Shaman or Cleric.<br>
<br>
2. Jaeil the Insane in The Hole.  Any group that can fight it's way done will own this Mob.  The nice thing is that it's spawned, and as many Ranger's as you want can do him in one trip.  I'll likely tag along with one of the bigger guilds who do this frequently for their Rangers.  Trouble is I need to do East Karana first.<br>
<br>
3. Stone from Plain of Sky.  Hard, because it's in Sky.  Fourth Island I think.  They are a very common drop, so lots of people have them sitting around.  I plan to MQ this unless.<br>
<br>
4.  VSR in KC.  An easy fight, one group if casters can rune the MT.  He drops two stones, I only need one, Druids also need this stone. (Greyleef?)  He is a timed spawn after VS is killed.  This is the hardest encounter because it requires a quick mobilization, and frequently a race to him.  I see this encounter as my biggest road block because of the competition.<br>
<br>
